Of 45 consecutive RCU patients screened, 20 (44%) met inclusion criteria and were randomly assigned to a study group. All 20 enrolled patients completed the 14-day trial (Figure 1
). There were no significant differences in baseline characteristics between the study groups (Table 1
). Overall, 90% of enrolled participants were either vitamin D insufficient (15–30 ng/mL; 50%) or vitamin D deficient (<15 ng/mL; 40%). All patients had albumin levels less than 3 g/dL. Calcium (corrected) and phosphorus levels were in the normal range.
